# Registry & Systems

## Three-Phase Loop

```
update (order 0–20)   → input, AI, movement, physics, collision, camera, animation
draw   (order 0)      → render pipeline (shadow + forward + post)
commit (order 0–100)  → flush input frame, record dt for FPS
```

Lower `order` runs first within a phase. Reserve bands:

| Band | Phase | Use |
|------|-------|-----|
| 0 | update | input toggles, debug |
| 4 | update | nav grid blocked-cell refresh when `navGrid.dirty` (`installNavGridSystem`) |
| 5 | update | player input, AI controller |
| 6 | update | test AI pathfinding (sandbox `installTestAiSystem`) |
| 7 | update | transform hierarchy (`installTransformHierarchySystem`) |
| 8 | update | collider world bake (`installColliderTransformSystem`), movement (intent → velocity, jump → FSM; blocks input while sliding) |
| 9–10 | update | CPU character physics (`installCharacterPhysicsSystem`: broadphase@9, integrate + `resolveCylinderMoveAndSlide`@10) |
| 12 | update | animation FSM (`installAnimationFsmSystem`) |
| 13 | update | character yaw (`installCharacterStateSystem`; skipped while `character.sliding`) |
| 0 | postUpdate | camera follow; GPU skeletal pose gather (`installSkeletalGpuPoseSystem`) |
| 0 | draw | render pipeline (pose encode + cull + forward) |
| 0 | commit | input.commitFrame() |
| 100 | commit | dt capture |

## Component Queries

```typescript
for (const e of registry.view(COMPONENT_KEYS.character)) { ... }

const colliders = registry.getComponentsByName(COMPONENT_KEYS.collider) as Collider[];
```

- `view(key)` — cached entity list; invalidated on register, deregister, add/remove component
- `getComponentsByName(key)` — flat component instance list for cross-entity deps (collision, raycasts)
- Never pass collider arrays or entity references to system installers

## System Installer Pattern

Every system is a standalone `install*System(registry, ...deps)` with one concern:

```typescript
export const installSpiderSystem = (registry: Registry) => {
  registry.addAction('update', (ctx) => {
    for (const e of registry.view(COMPONENT_KEYS.spiderAI)) {
      // ...
    }
  }, 5);
};
```

Install scene systems on the scene registry. Install game-level systems (render pipeline, global input) on the game registry.

## Entity Composition

```typescript
const entity = registry.createBare();
entity.components[COMPONENT_KEYS.transform] = createTransform();
entity.components[COMPONENT_KEYS.spiderAI] = createSpiderAI();
registry.register(entity);
```

Never call `register` before components are attached — `registry.create()` is an alias for `createBare()` and does not index components.

Components are data-only. Behaviour lives exclusively in system installers.

## Scene manager

`installSceneManager` in `sandbox/src/globals/sceneManager.ts` owns level transitions:

```typescript
await sceneManager.switchTo('testOne');
```

Sequence: unload previous → `gltfCache.preload(urls)` → `useLevelScene` → `game.setActiveScene` → `await scene.load()`. Always creates a **fresh** scene per level id.

Digit1–4 hard-switch to the seeded test levels (`testOne`–`testFour`). Level select opens from the sandbox main menu (Load Level). Levels resolve from `construct.levelLocalStore` via `parseLevelFile`. Prop spawn uses engine `instantiateProp` from `viberanium/spawn`.

Install on the **game registry**. Scene systems install on each ephemeral scene registry inside `createPlayableScene`.
## Nav grid system

`installNavGridSystem(registry)` runs at update order **4** — before test AI (6) and movement (8).

```typescript
export const installNavGridSystem = (registry: Registry) => {
  registry.addAction('update', () => {
    for (const e of registry.view(COMPONENT_KEYS.navGrid)) {
      const grid = e.components[COMPONENT_KEYS.navGrid] as NavGridComponent;
      if (!grid.dirty) continue;

      const colliders = registry.getComponentsByName(COMPONENT_KEYS.collider) as Collider[];
      updateNavGridBlocked(grid, colliders, grid.agentRadius);
      grid.dirty = false;
    }
  }, 4);
};
```

### When to mark dirty

Call `markNavGridDirty(registry)` after any change to static scene colliders:

| Trigger | Example |
|---------|---------|
| Collider added | `instantiateProp` after `registry.register` |
| Colliders removed at runtime | Destructible props, doors (future) |

`unload()` destroys the nav grid entity — no `markNavGridDirty` needed on teardown.

### AI pathfinding

Sandbox `installTestAiSystem` reads the scene nav grid — it does not build or cache its own. Install order: `installNavGridSystem` before `installTestAiSystem` so blocked cells are fresh when `dirty` was set the same frame.

Sandbox `createPlayableScene` installs `installSkeletalCharacterSystems` (not a monolithic animation system).

## Skeletal character systems

`installSkeletalCharacterSystems(registry, { device, setPreDrawEncode?, getLodOrigin? })` requires a GPU device and installs hierarchy, FSM, and batched GPU pose only (no CPU pose/mesh/attachment fallback).

| Installer | Phase | Writes |
|-----------|-------|--------|
| `installTransformHierarchySystem` | update | child `transform.world` from `localTransform` |
| `installAnimationFsmSystem` | update | `animationStateMachine` state + timers |
| `installSkeletalGpuPoseSystem` | postUpdate gather; draw encode | GPU joint palettes + mesh/attachment models |

Install `installCharacterStateSystem`, `installMovementSystem`, `installColliderTransformSystem`, and `installCharacterPhysicsSystem` separately on the scene registry. Character collision is CPU via `installCharacterPhysicsSystem` (broadphase query + cylinder `resolveCylinderMoveAndSlide`); GPU pose/cull/render stay unchanged.

## Character collision systems

Sandbox `createPlayableScene` installs the CPU collision stack only — not `installCollisionSystem` (optional GPU alternate).

| Installer | Order | Role |
|-----------|-------|------|
| `installColliderTransformSystem` | 8 | Bake static `localShape` → world `shape` when `transform.dirty` |
| `installMovementSystem` | 8 | `movementIntent` → `character.velocity`; project onto `groundNormal` when `onGround`; zero input while `sliding` |
| `installCharacterPhysicsSystem` | 9–10 | Fixed substep (`1/144` s, max 4); gravity when `!onGround && !sliding`; integrate; `resolveCylinderMoveAndSlide`; update `onGround` / `sliding` / `groundNormal` / `slideSpeed` |
| `installCharacterStateSystem` | 13 | Yaw toward movement intent — skipped while sliding |

### Slope and slide behavior

No `ramp` type — rotated box colliders act as ramps. Contact normals classify surfaces:

- **Walkable floor** (`normalY ≥ cos(floorMaxAngle)`): `onGround`, movement follows `groundNormal`
- **Slide slope** (`cos(80°) < normalY < cos(floorMaxAngle)`): `sliding`, downhill `applySlideVelocity`, input blocked
- **Wall** (else): velocity projected along wall tangent (`slideVelocityOnWall`)

Pure collision math lives in `viberanium/collision/characterContact.ts` and `characterCollision.ts`. Systems query obstacles per character via broadphase — never pass collider arrays into installers.
